This paper discusses the security of open-world decentralized systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the role of rationality in attacking these systems, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also touches on information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) in its discussion of rationality and decision-making.
